dc_title_s: Hudson's Strait shewing the track of H.M.S. Terror, in 1836-7
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Depth shown by soundings. Includes Hudson Strait, Hudson Bay, Foxe Channel, Repulse Bay, and Roes Welcome Sound. Surveyed, conjectured, and unknown portions of coastline are shown. Dates of voyage shown along marked route. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 7 (1837), pp. 457-66; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v. 7 1837
dc_publisher_s: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1837.
dc_subject_sm: Hudson Strait (Québec and Nunavut)—Discovery and exploration—Maps
